<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Former Big Brother star Krystal Forscutt welcomed her third child, a son named Huska, on Friday. </p>

<p>And on Monday, the 34-year-old introduced the newborn to his siblings, Nakoda, two, and Sunny, five. </p>

<p>In an Instagram Stories video, and multiple photos, the delighted children cuddled up to their new brother, gently cradling him. </p>

<p>New addition: Former Big Brother star Krystal Forscutt welcomed her third child, a son named Huska, on Friday. Both pictured </p>

<p>Dressed in matching burnt orange outfits, Nakoda and Sunny were gentle with the little one, curiously reaching out to touch his little limbs and give him a kiss. </p>

<p>Krystal captioned the sweet video: 'It was love at first sight'. </p>

<p>On Sunday, the former reality star revealed she'd undergone her third painkiller-free labour, despite suffering from internal bleeding this time around.   </p>

<p>Krystal described what it was like to give birth to her 'big boy, who weighed 4.28kgs [9.4lbs], revealing that she suffered 'little bit of damage' due to internal bleeding.</p>

<p>Sweet! And on Monday, the 34-year-old introduced the newborn to his siblings, Nakoda, two, and Sunny, five</p>

<p>Curious: Dressed in matching burnt orange outfits, Nakoda and Sunny were gentle with the little one, curiously reaching out to touch his tiny limbs </p>

<p>Big brother: Sunny gave his little brother a sweet kiss on the forehead </p>

<p>Krystal captioned the sweet video: 'It was love at first sight'</p>

<p>So proud! Sunny was protective with his tiny new brother </p>

<p>She insisted, however: 'Every ounce of pain couldn't be more worth it for the gift in the form of this beautiful little boy.'  </p>

<p>Krystal also said she was pleased to have the support of husband Neil Hipwell while giving birth.   </p>

<p>'I was so happy to have [Neil] by my side supporting me, I actually can't believe I let him come near me this time. I may have pushed his hand off my legs a couple of times though'.    </p>

<p>'Every ounce of pain couldn't be more worth it': Krystal Forscutt revealed she gave birth to newborn son Huska without using painkillers - despite suffering from internal bleeding. Pictured: Krystal giving birth on Friday with husband Neil</p>

<p>So happy! 'So far Huska has been an absolute joy! We are feeling so completely blissed out and just so incredibly blessed to have our Husky boy earth side' she said</p>

<p>She added: 'So far Huska has been an absolute joy! We are feeling so completely blissed out and just so incredibly blessed to have our Husky boy earth side.'        </p>

<p>Krystal announced on Saturday that she and Neil welcomed a baby boy named Huska Hipwell. </p>

<p>Krystal shared a sweet black-and-white video on Instagram announcing the news, saying: 'He's here and we are beyond obsessed.'</p>

<p>'He's here': On Saturday, Krystal announced the birth of her third child with husband Neil</p>

<p>Smitten: In a video clip, Krystal can be seen doting over her baby while in hospital and gazing at him affectionately</p>

<p>Krystal revealed she was expecting her third child in March, but was told by doctors to be 'cautiously optimistic' about the pregnancy.</p>

<p>She almost suffered a miscarriage at 13 weeks, which would have been her third if complications persisted.</p>

<p>She and Neil are based in Sydney's Cronulla with their family, including their children, Nakoda and Sunny.</p>

